 self-study. Together with the large amount of practical information provided by the book, they also enable architects to become familiar with grading as an important design element of landscape architecture.  aHistory, forms of terrain, basic principles, digital modeling, slope reinforcement systems, construction site implementation, and practical examples—all are treated in detail by the author. Short problems, systematically organized, enable the reader to apply what he or she has learned.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGrading (Earthwork). 0aLandscape architecturexTechnique. 0aLandscape construction. 0aSoil compactionxElectronic books. 0aSoil compaction. 4aGrading. 4aLandscape Modelling. 4aLandscape architecture. 4aTerrain Modelling. 7aARCHITECTURE / Landscape.2bisacsh1 aRead, Jessica.1 aWalker, Peter.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ARTS AND ARCHITECTURE 2008z978311031899908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET KUNST UND ARCHITEKTUR 2008z9783110318890oZDB-23-DKA40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303460987640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783034609876423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783034609876/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-031899-9  E-BOOK PACKAGE ARTS AN